In Node.js, you can calculate `2+2` using the built-in arithmetic operations. Here's a simple example of how you might do this:

```javascript
// Calculate 2 + 2
const result = 2 + 2;

// Output the result
console.log(result);
```

When you run this code, it will print `4` to the console. Node.js handles basic arithmetic operations like addition in the same way as JavaScript does in the browser.
